Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta and
cavolo nero.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #frying pan over medium-high
heat.

Add the @pork sausage meat{225%g} and cook until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Break it up into small chunks with a #wooden spoon as it cooks.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces.

Pick the @sage{1/2%bunch}(leaves picked and roughly chopped) from their stalks and
roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Add the chopped onion and sage to the #pan with the sausagemeat. Cook, stirring
often, until the onion begins to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook until
tender, ~{8%minutes}.

When the sausagemeat is browned and the onion softened stir in the
@chicken stock powder{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} and lower the heat to a simmer.
Cook until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When the pasta has 5 mins left add the @chopped cavolo nero{100%g} to the pan.
Cook for ~{5%minutes}, then drain the pasta and cavolo nero in a #colander.

> Ensure the kale is completely submerged in the water - pop a lid on the pan if
> you need to.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} into the sauce and bring to the boil. Remove from
the heat.

Taste the creamy sauce, reheat and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if necessary.

Mix the sauce and pasta together and share between your #bowls.

Finish with a sprinkle of @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated). Dig in!